{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b1e00d6c-d5eb-4dda-b299-e4b9dbed85fa","content":"Here are the common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (dotnet)**\n- Template: `dotnet new webapi`\n- Auth options via `--auth`:\n  - `None` – no auth (default)\n  - `Individual` – local user accounts (ASP.NET Identity)\n  - `IndividualB2C` – Azure AD B2C\n  - `SingleOrg` – Azure AD (single tenant)\n  - `MultiOrg` – Azure AD (multi-tenant)\n  - `Windows` – Windows/NTLM/Kerberos\n\n**Node.js / Express**\n- Use `express-generator` or start from scratch\n- Auth via libraries: Passport.js, express-jwt, OAuth2 middleware\n\n**Python / FastAPI or Django**\n- FastAPI: use `python-jose` + OAuth2 password/bearer flows\n- Django REST Framework: token auth, session, OAuth (django-oauth-toolkit)\n\n**Java / Spring Boot**\n- Template: Spring Initializr with \"Spring Security\"\n- Auth: JWT, OAuth2 Resource Server, LDAP, SAML\n\nWhich stack are you targeting? I can scaffold a project for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"08651cb4-43e7-4407-9657-42ba0b75a1c9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the main options.","outputTokens":345,"requestId":"A80C:1BE3:C8E7F1:E35CFB:6A027924"},"id":"40138582-e653-4d6c-8014-02bb952c1b62","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:49:49.314Z","parentId":"9362fe2c-2e54-45d2-882c-8c967262b168"}
